The latter encapsulates third-party callback-based APIs into a `ReplaySubject` of size 1. `DriverService#getDriver` publishes the subject as an observable. ```javascript   constructor(driverService: DriverService) {     this.driver$ = driverService.getDriver();   }   findAll(): Observable<ChangeSet[]> {     return this.driver$       .pipe(         filter((driver: OptionalDriver) => driver !== NO_DRIVER),         map((driver: OptionalDriver) => driver as Driver),         mergeMap((driver: Driver) => {           const session = driver.rxSession();           return session             .readTransaction(LiquibaseService.readChangeSets)             .pipe(               finalize(() => session.close())             );         })       );   } ``` When the connection switches to the correct database, `mergeMap` returns a value: an array of 1 `ChangeSet` as it should. However, the strange thing is that the component DOM never changes, it always displays the `#noActiveConnection` block.
